  "time_ut": 1661335894,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Thailand's Prime Minister suspended",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The country's Constitutional Court decided today (24) to suspend the tenure of the Prime Minister of Thailand, Prayuth Chan-o-cha.",
        "The Constitutional Court suspended the tenure of the Prime Minister while hearing a petition submitted by the opposition political groups on tenure.",
        "Taiwanese media have reported that Prawit Wong Suwan, who served as Deputy Prime Minister after the temporary suspension of the position of Prayuth Chan-o-cha, who is also a former army general, will begin his duties as caretaker Prime Minister.",
        "In 2014, General Prayuth Chan-o-cha was the Chief of Army Staff of Thailand. Considering the instability in Thai politics at that time, General Prayuth Chan-o-cha led the army and seized power in the country through a coup. And without any bloodshed.",
        "General Prayuth Chan-o-cha served as the head of the military junta that was established for 5 years. However, in 2019, he took steps to hold a general election confirming democracy.",
        "Prayuth Chan-o-cha, who had resigned as army commander, ran as a civilian and won by rallying pro-military political groups. Sworn in as a civilian Prime Minister, Prayuth Chan-o-cha took office in July 2019.",
        "According to the Thai constitution, the term of office of the Prime Minister of Thailand is 8 years. Thai opposition groups had continuously pointed out that Prayuth Chan-o-cha's tenure as Prime Minister would end today (24), as he served as both a military commander and a civilian.",
        "The opposition political groups pointed that out in a petition to the Constitutional Court. Accordingly, the court decided to suspend Prayuth Chan-o-cha's tenure.",
        "The Constitutional Court, which is set to hear the petition, will extend its tenure as head of the military junta to its tenure as civilian prime minister.",
        "It also says that Prayuth Chan-o-cha will be able to continue as Prime Minister if it is ruled impossible to add."
      ],
